<br>
frog crown<br>
65hp/65 mana neck<br>
45hp/45 mana ears*2<br>
fungi tunic or Iksar BP<br>
6 AC/65hp rings<br>
Gaunts of The Iron Tactics<br>
Military Kromriff Leggings<br>
FBSS<br>
Sarnak Battleshield<br>
Ringed Mace of Ykesha or Jade Mace<br>
<br>
Hmm, what else?<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uplendil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Plendil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/9/01 12:00:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:  Druidic melee equip</span><hr size=1> Try a Heirophant crook...<br>
<br>
with a FBSS, and dex gear, you get a 246hp proc 2-3x during a mele fight. It really adds up...of course you'll be WELL LOVED by the mobs. Be sure and not do this near a bunch of mobs as it is an AoE proc.<br>
<br>
Plendil <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukewgarblackhawke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kewgar Blackhawke</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/9/01 2:58:51 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:  Druidic melee equip</span><hr size=1> You said &quot;no nodrop&quot;  and then you list the Kromrif Military leggings which are nodrop =P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugleam.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gleam</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/11/01 1:41:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> LOL</span><hr size=1> Yep. I should have said 'no no-drop except for stuff I forgot that it was no-drop' <br>
:) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubatou062671.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Batou062671</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/11/01 2:12:30 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:  Druidic melee equip</span><hr size=1> While the 65hp/mana neck is nice, it has no AC on it.  If you really want to increase your tanking abality, you should increase your AC before hitpoints.  Both if possible but I think AC is much more helpfull in avoiding damage in the first place.<br>
<br>
Not sure which 45hp/mana earrings you mean but the electrum black sapphire earrings are 2ac/35hp/25 mana and are very nice. <p>Batou Thornhill<BR>
Wanderer of the 54th Season<BR>
Harbingers<BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucountesskrak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CountessKrak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/13/01 7:46:26 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:  Druidic melee equip</span><hr size=1> Druid and melee are mutually exclusive. When will you people ever learn? Druid bashes Phar Dar for 1 damage. Phar Dar hits Druid for a total of 2000 damage. Got the picture now?  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uflaim.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Flaim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/13/01 3:22:31 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:  Druidic melee equip</span><hr size=1> Druids can bash?<br>
