Bristlebane </font></b></font> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urandomuser.showPublicProfile?language=EN>random user</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/15/01 10:54:56 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:  Druidic melee equip</span><hr size=1> Well, though potentially disguised, the necklace (and other items) comes down to whether you are being powerleveled or if you are trying to porcupine.<br>
<br>
If you are being powerleveled, then the 65/65 necklace is better.  Along with that I would try to get an ulthork hide collar (8 ac, 30 hp, -30 mana), bracer of vejaan (ac 10 some resists), azure sleeves, gator legs, hooded black cloak or heiro cloak, obulous death shroud (high ac, some sta, though i'm not sure 1 sta = 3 hp at low levels... probably not... so maybe tattered mantle instead), tree weave (if you can wear it), barbed dragonscale boots (if you can afford it heh) or something like dwarven workboots otherwise, froggie crown, enshrouded veil (nice ac and hp), coldain skin gloves (if you can afford it) or ES gauntlets, electrum black sapphire earrings (2ac, 35hp, 25 mana), velium fire opal rings, and an idol of the thorned (high ac, high sta).<br>
<br>
If you are just trying to porcupine, then just get whatever high ac stuff you can.  Here's a list sorted by AC(primary)/Wis(secondary)<br>
